HEADWORD: Neuration
<hw>Neu*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>The arrangement or distribution of nerves, as in the leaves of a
plant or the wings of an insect; nervation; venation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

